The paper proposes a new algorithm that combines Swarm Intelligence and Evolutionary mechanisms to solve optimization problems. This makes it likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of complex functions and optimization control problems, which are common in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) categories. The paper also compares its results with standard Genetic Algorithms (GAs), which are commonly studied in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Robotics (cs.RO) categories. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.LG, and cs.RO.
